## Vertical Integration
# Geranium Limited (Nigeria)

The powerhouse of local sourcing and operational excellence. With deep roots in Nigeria’s agricultural heartlands, we manage sustainable procurement, logistics, and on-ground execution. Our local expertise ensures quality raw materials while generating employment and supporting community development.

# Geranium International LLC (Florida, USA)

Our US-based entity serves as the global gateway for international distribution, regulatory compliance (FDA, EU standards, etc.), investor relations, and access to premium markets in North America, Europe, and beyond. We handle offtake agreements, quality certification, and seamless cross-border operations.

### Phase 1 Industrial Value Addition
## Phase 1: Industrial Value Addition – Agro-Processing

We are executing a strategic transition from exporting raw commodities to producing high-margin, refined industrial ingredients. By investing in modern processing facilities, Geranium Group captures greater value, ensures consistent quality, reduces supply chain risks, and creates skilled jobs in Nigeria.

# Palm Oil

State-of-the-art refining and fractionation facilities producing premium crude and refined palm oil for industrial applications (food processing, oleochemicals, cosmetics) and consumer markets. Our controlled processing delivers superior stability, purity, and traceability.

# Soya Oil

Advanced extraction and refining lines yielding high-protein soya meal for livestock and aquaculture feed, alongside refined soya oil for edible and industrial use. We leverage Nigeria’s growing soybean production to deliver consistent, high-quality output.

# Sesame Seeds

Modern cleaning, dehulling, sorting, and oil-pressing technology that meets stringent international culinary, pharmaceutical, and cosmetic standards. Our sesame products boast high oil content, low moisture, and excellent purity — ideal for export to Europe, Asia, and the Middle East.

## Strategic Goal:

“To transform raw harvests into premium, export-ready industrial ingredients — boosting local employment, increasing foreign exchange earnings, and delivering superior margins for our partners.”

